{
  "texts": [
    "However, some challenges need to be addressed, such as technology integration, security, data utilization, and costs.",
    "Further research is necessary to develop comprehensive frameworks that consider technological, economic, and social perspectives on IoT in agriculture (Hassan et al. 2024).",
    "IoT technology plays a crucial role in enhancing agricultural efficiency through data-driven decisions and automated irrigation (Bhandari et al. 2023; Cihan 2023; Seetha et al. 2023; Sharma et al. 2023).",
    "By utilizing IoT devices like soil sensors, drones, and satellite imagery, farmers can gather targeted information about farm conditions, such as soil moisture, temperature, and crop health.",
    "This enables them to make informed decisions, optimize resource utilization, and enhance crop yields."
  ]
}